import re
from typing import List, Dict

def extract_entities(text: str, schema: List[str]) -> Dict:
    entities = {category: [] for category in schema}
    # Patterns for each entity type
    software_system_pattern = r"\b[A-Z][a-z-]+?\b"
    physical_device_pattern = r"\b[a-z]+ device\b"
    environment_object_pattern = r"\b[a-z]+ object\b"
    external_system_pattern = r"\bexternal system\b"
    system_requirement_pattern = r"\brequirement\b"
    shared_phenomena_pattern = r"\bshared phenomenon\b"
    
    # Split text into sentences
    sentences = re.split(r'\.|\?|,|;', text)
    
    for sentence in sentences:
        sentence = sentence.strip()
        if not sentence:
            continue
        # Find all matches for each entity type
        software_system_matches = re.findall(software_system_pattern, sentence)
        physical_device_matches = re.findall(physical_device_pattern, sentence)
        environment_object_matches = re.findall(environment_object_pattern, sentence)
        external_system_matches = re.findall(external_system_pattern, sentence)
        system_requirement_matches = re.findall(system_requirement_pattern, sentence)
        shared_phenomena_matches = re.findall(shared_phenomena_pattern, sentence)
        
        # Update the entities
        entities['Software System'] += software_system_matches
        entities['Physical Device'] += physical_device_matches
        entities['Environment Object'] += environment_object_matches
        entities['External System'] += external_system_matches
        entities['System Requirements'] += system_requirement_matches
        entities['Shared Phenomena'] += shared_phenomena_matches
        
    # Remove duplicates by converting to set and back to list
    for category in entities:
        entities[category] = list(set(entities[category]))
    
    return entities
